## Analysis of `pcap_findalldevs`

The `pcap_findalldevs` function is responsible for discovering and listing all available network interfaces on the system that can be used for packet capture. It achieves this by first querying the platform-specific mechanisms (`pcap_platform_finddevs`) to find local network interfaces. Then, it iterates through a list of other potential capture source types (e.g., remote capture, virtual interfaces) and calls their respective `findalldevs_op` functions to discover any interfaces they might expose. The function aggregates all discovered interfaces into a linked list and returns a pointer to the head of this list via the `alldevsp` parameter. If any error occurs during the discovery process, the function cleans up any partially constructed list and returns an error code.

